cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category as it deals with ad retrieval in sponsored search platforms. The use of personalized information and historical ad click data also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) categories. The hierarchical network approach and the use of weights on edges suggest that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. Finally, the use of personalized information and the focus on e-commerce suggest that it may belong to the Computers and Society (cs.CY) category.
